The paper deals with the problem of finding vertex-disjoint paths in planar graphs, which is a classic problem in graph theory and algorithms. The problem is known to be NP-hard in general graphs, but there are some special cases where polynomial-time algorithms are known. The paper focuses on the case where all terminals are on a common face, which is a natural and important special case. The paper uses techniques from graph theory, combinatorics, and computational geometry, which are typical of the subfields of cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.GT, cs.DM, and cs.CC.
